summary: ‘The other David’. Indeed. Or rather, fuck yeah! Lady, you have good taste, I have decided.   Also, Tennant is absolutely lovely...
question: ‘The other David’. Indeed. Or rather, fuck yeah! Lady, you have good taste, I have decided.   Also, Tennant is absolutely lovely irl. I met him at Stratford when he was doing Hamlet there. I’d taken a group of students to a performance workshop as part of a field trip and he randomly showed up to say hi. The kids got autographs and pictures and he told me how vitally important it was that English teachers still tried to pass on a love of Shakespeare to their students. I was super impressed.
answer:
Haha, yeah he is the “other” David cause David Duchovny is simply my original David. A friend of mine is a huge David Tennant fan and when we were both talking about our Davids I needed to distinguish the two somehow 😁

Oh yes, he is so lovely. I have only seen him at comic cons and once at a stage door, but he’s so great. He’s so sweet and listens to every one. A real sweetheart. Intelligent, too. He’s a huge Shakespearr fan anyway if I remember correctly! So that doesn’t surprise me.

VIDEO: Watch David Tennant & Krysten Ritter's Comic Con Panel  



Jessica Jones co-stars David Tennant and Krysten Ritter took...
caption:
VIDEO: Watch David Tennant & Krysten Ritter’s Comic Con Panel 

Jessica Jones co-stars David Tennant and Krysten Ritter took part in a joint Q&A panel yesterday during their appearance at Arizona’s ACE Comic Con. During the event at the Gila River Arena in Glendale, they discssed the Marvel TV show and answered questions from audience members.

You can watch the full panel moderated by Angélique Roché here, including David’s account of how Krysten nearly broke his nose on set during one complex scene from Season Two.
